---
import Container from '../ui/Container.astro';
---

<section id="faq" class="py-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
  <Container>
    
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
        Frequently asked questions
      </h2>
      
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Everything you need to know about Zeyn. Can't find the answer you're looking for? 
        <a href="/contact" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Reach out to our team</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        
        <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq1')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              How is Zeyn different from Microsoft Word or Google Docs?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq1-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq1" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Unlike traditional word processors that are designed for documents, Zeyn is built specifically for novel writing. 
              We focus on distraction-free writing with features like zen mode, chapter organization, progress tracking, and 
              goal setting. You won't find unnecessary formatting options or business document features—just the tools you 
              need to write your story.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq2')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              Can I import my existing manuscript from Word or other apps?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq2-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq2" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Yes! Zeyn supports importing from Word (.docx), Google Docs, plain text (.txt), and Markdown (.md) files. 
              Simply drag and drop your files or use the import function. The app will intelligently break your content 
              into chapters if it detects chapter headings, or you can organize it manually after import.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq3')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              Is my data safe? What happens if I lose internet connection?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq3-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq3" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Your data is automatically saved locally on your device every few seconds, so you never lose work even without 
              internet. With a Professional or Team subscription, your projects are also continuously synced to the cloud with 
              enterprise-grade encryption. We use the same security standards as banks, and you can export your data at any time.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq4')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              Can I use Zeyn offline?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq4-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq4" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Absolutely! Zeyn works completely offline. All your writing, editing, and organization features are available 
              without an internet connection. Your work is saved locally, and when you reconnect, any cloud sync (if you have 
              a paid plan) will automatically update your backup.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq5')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              What export formats are supported?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq5-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq5" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              All plans support PDF and Word (.docx) export. Professional and Team plans also include EPUB for ebook publishing, 
              Markdown, HTML, and plain text. You can export individual chapters, selected scenes, or your entire manuscript 
              with custom formatting options for different publishing requirements.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq6')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              Is there a mobile app?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq6-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq6" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Yes! Zeyn is available on iOS, Android, Windows, macOS, and Linux. The web version works on any device with a 
              modern browser. All versions sync seamlessly with your paid plan, so you can write on your laptop at home 
              and continue on your phone during your commute.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq7')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              How does the goal tracking feature work?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq7-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq7" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Set daily word count goals, track writing streaks, and celebrate milestones. Zeyn shows your progress with 
              beautiful charts and gives you encouraging notifications when you hit targets. You can set different goals 
              for weekdays vs weekends, and the app learns your writing patterns to give personalized recommendations.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq8')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              Can I collaborate with other writers or editors?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq8-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq8" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              The Team plan includes real-time collaboration features. Invite up to 5 collaborators per project. They can 
              leave comments, suggest edits, and work on different chapters simultaneously. You maintain full control over 
              who can view or edit each project, and there's a complete revision history so you never lose previous versions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 9 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq9')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              What happens if I want to cancel my subscription?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq9-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq9" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              You can cancel anytime with no questions asked. Your account will remain active until the end of your billing 
              period, then automatically switch to the free Starter plan. You keep all your projects and can export everything. 
              If you change your mind, you can resubscribe and pick up exactly where you left off.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 10 -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors" 
                  onclick="toggleFAQ('faq10')">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              Do you offer support for screenwriters or non-fiction authors?
            </span>
            <svg id="faq10-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div id="faq10" class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              While Zeyn is optimized for novel writing, many screenwriters and non-fiction authors love the distraction-free 
              environment and organizational tools. We're working on specialized templates for screenplays and academic writing. 
              If you have specific needs, let us know—we build features based on user feedback!
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Still have questions -->
    <div class="text-center mt-12">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
        Still have questions?
      </h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
        Our support team is here to help you succeed with your writing goals.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors font-medium rounded-lg">
          Contact support
          <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/help" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors font-medium rounded-lg">
          Browse help docs
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </Container>
</section>

<script>
  declare global {
    interface Window {
      toggleFAQ: (id: string) => void;
    }
  }
  
  window.toggleFAQ = function(id: string) {
    const faqContent = document.getElementById(id);
    const faqIcon = document.getElementById(id + '-icon');
    
    if (faqContent && faqIcon) {
      if (faqContent.classList.contains('hidden')) {
        faqContent.classList.remove('hidden');
        faqIcon.classList.add('rotate-180');
      } else {
        faqContent.classList.add('hidden');
        faqIcon.classList.remove('rotate-180');
      }
    }
  }
</script>